      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALL THE WAY MAE (4) bounced off her excellent first-up third with a comprehensive 2.75 len win at Kembla Grange over this journey. Can stalk the good speed from the sticky gate and prove hard to hold out again. CHARLINA (2) just under a month between runs when she showed blistering speed to lead throughout over this track and trip in grand style. Kept fresh again and expected to go close despite the 2kg weight rise. IRON FURY (3) resumes after holding his own in this class when last in work. Closed strongly with the 58kg for a tidy second over 1100m here last December. Looks ready to go with the two trials and will relish the 2kg claim. TIDES TURNING (6) surprise winner two-back at Hawkesbury, then jumped in grade with a plugging seventh over 1100m at Hawkesbury. In-form apprentice hops aboard and can return to form.",
